{
  "stem": "7506.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't remember my parents complaining about-- they may indeed have done that to other adults.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But never to me as a child.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's difficult for me to-- not to remember, but to think that I was a child those days.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It singled us out because, [? hell, ?] the things that I've already told you.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Also, that the-- the adults had to have an identity card which had a big 'J' stamp next to their photograph.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Dutch, it was known as a [DUTCH].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And of course, it singled us out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "From before the war, no Christmas trees.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] Then stop being having to go-- being able to go to school and having to go to school, as was the law.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "No more bicycles.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then, of course, as the time went on, my parents-- I heard my parents talking that people had been put on 'transport'-- that's the-- that's the literal translation of the Dutch word, which is very similar-- and had been sent away.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Or the word was called-- another word that was used-- Dutch word was [DUTCH].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "That Dutch means 'collected.' And another place that was identified and one [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] obtained knowledge from was the [DUTCH].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The [DUTCH] was before the war, a theater [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that became a place where the Jews were picked up on the [DUTCH] taken to, kept in this [DUTCH], in the theater, until they were transported to the east.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, as a child at that time, thought, especially when my [SIGHS] grandparents were gone and my other family-- I thought they'd been taken to places in Germany in east-- because Germany is east from Holland-- to work.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that's all I knew.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
